I" <p>Haskell and Elm employ pattern matching.</p>

<p>Parsing <em>is</em> pattern matching.</p>

<p>PEG is my favourite parsing tool, A.T.M.</p>

<p>Ohm-JS is my favourite PEG A.T.M.</p>

<h2 id="dsls-for-pattern-matching">DSLs for Pattern Matching</h2>

<p>REGEX is a DSL for line-oriented pattern matching.</p>

<p>PEG is a DSL for structure-oriented pattern matching.</p>

<h2 id="fractalizing-fp">Fractalizing FP</h2>

<p>Haskell (and Elm, etc.) could be decomposed into two components:</p>

<ol>
  <li>parsing</li>
  <li>the rest</li>
</ol>
